    public class NoisierDefaultListableBeanFactory
extends org.springframework.beans.factory.support.DefaultListableBeanFactory
    In Spring 1.2.6 and 1.2.8, when there's a problem pre-instantiating any singleton bean, all existing singleton beans are immediately destroyed. Unfortunately for developers, this destruction occurs without any explanation: neither the problematic bean's name nor the error stack is logged. This subclasses the default bean factory to log the failing bean's name and a stack trace of the exception.
